Package: prediction
Type: Package
Title: Tidy, Type-Safe 'prediction()' Methods
Description: A one-function package containing prediction(), a type-safe alternative to predict() that always returns a data frame. The summary() method provides a data frame with average predictions, possibly over counterfactual versions of the data (Ã  la the margins command in 'Stata'). Marginal effect estimation is provided by the related package, 'margins' <https://cran.r-project.org/package=margins>. The package currently supports common model types (e.g., lm, glm) from the 'stats' package, as well as numerous other model classes from other add-on packages. See the README file or main package documentation page for a complete listing.
